( knocking )

16:28.822 --> 16:30.281
Hang on.

16:30.281 --> 16:31.950
Hurry.

16:30.281 --> 16:31.950
JANE: You're good on time.

16:31.950 --> 16:33.701
Legal docs for

16:31.950 --> 16:33.701
Jane Villanueva.

16:33.701 --> 16:35.912
Van, it's a messenger

16:33.701 --> 16:35.912
with documents

16:35.912 --> 16:38.665
from the publishing house

16:35.912 --> 16:38.665
for me to sign.

16:38.665 --> 16:39.916
Shut up. Oh, my God!

16:39.916 --> 16:42.084
<i>Chloe's favorite</i>

16:39.916 --> 16:42.084
<i>massage therapist?</i>

16:42.084 --> 16:43.795
She wants something

16:42.084 --> 16:43.795
called the pounder?

16:43.795 --> 16:45.546
Oh, no.

16:43.795 --> 16:45.546
VAN: Yep.

16:45.546 --> 16:47.256
Did I mention

16:45.546 --> 16:47.256
Gary finally dropped us?

16:47.256 --> 16:49.634
He's taking his next book

16:47.256 --> 16:49.634
to HarperCollins.

16:49.634 --> 16:51.344
Uh, 90 minutes with Mary.

16:51.344 --> 16:53.220
Van, let me call you back.

16:53.220 --> 16:54.973
( in Spanish ):

16:53.220 --> 16:54.973
What's wrong?

16:54.973 --> 16:56.975
( in English ):

16:54.973 --> 16:56.975
I-It's about when

16:54.973 --> 16:56.975
I get paid for my novel.

16:56.975 --> 17:01.270
NARRATOR:

16:56.975 --> 17:01.270
<i>And that's when Jane</i>

16:56.975 --> 17:01.270
<i>finally got her check.</i>

17:01.270 --> 17:04.524
I don't get $50,000

17:01.270 --> 17:04.524
all at once.

17:04.524 --> 17:05.900
I get $5,000 now,

17:05.900 --> 17:07.944
another five

17:05.900 --> 17:07.944
when I turn in my first draft,

17:07.944 --> 17:11.698
and the rest after

17:07.944 --> 17:11.698
the book is published.

17:11.698 --> 17:14.283
Holy crap! I just quit my job.

17:14.283 --> 17:16.703
I need to get my job back!

17:20.206 --> 17:22.500
( groans ):

17:20.206 --> 17:22.500
Of course I need to get it back.

17:22.500 --> 17:24.168
Why? You hate

17:22.500 --> 17:24.168
that job.

17:24.168 --> 17:26.420
ABBEY:

17:24.168 --> 17:26.420
You<i> have</i> been

17:24.168 --> 17:26.420
complaining about it forever.

17:26.420 --> 17:27.964
NARRATOR:

17:26.420 --> 17:27.964
<i>Oops. Sorry. My bad again.</i>

17:27.964 --> 17:29.256
Maybe this could be

17:27.964 --> 17:29.256
a good thing.

17:29.256 --> 17:30.591
It's just that

17:29.256 --> 17:30.591
publishing jobs

17:30.591 --> 17:32.760
are so hard to find,

17:30.591 --> 17:32.760
especially in Miami.

17:32.760 --> 17:35.471
And I know Chloe hasn't

17:32.760 --> 17:35.471
filled my position yet.

17:35.471 --> 17:36.806
Here's a thought.

17:36.806 --> 17:38.516
Our new lounge manager

17:36.806 --> 17:38.516
isn't working out.

17:38.516 --> 17:40.894
You could replace him.

17:38.516 --> 17:40.894
Oh... God, no.

17:40.894 --> 17:43.688
Why not?

17:40.894 --> 17:43.688
I left waitressing behind.

17:43.688 --> 17:45.481
This isn't waitressing,

17:43.688 --> 17:45.481
this is management.

17:45.481 --> 17:47.191
This is a step up

17:45.481 --> 17:47.191
in responsibility and pay.

17:47.191 --> 17:50.069
A wrong step.

17:47.191 --> 17:50.069
A step backwards, or sideways.

17:52.030 --> 17:54.365
Mateo, use your words.

17:54.365 --> 17:56.158
Help me!

17:56.158 --> 17:57.493
Please.

17:57.493 --> 17:59.620
Please!

17:59.620 --> 18:04.166
I just need to do some intense

17:59.620 --> 18:04.166
groveling, and...hope it works.

18:04.166 --> 18:06.794
Okay, the basket's

18:04.166 --> 18:06.794
all done.

18:06.794 --> 18:08.880
NARRATOR:

18:06.794 --> 18:08.880
<i>Aw. Jane's first</i>

18:06.794 --> 18:08.880
<i>apology basket.</i>

